fields.description:
In the Database Configuration settings (Admin > Databases), the test connection button shows an invalid message when the database is not using a Unicode encoding.

It says:
{noformat}
The database is case insensitive. Crucible requires that the database use a case sensitive collation
{noformat}
whereas, to reflect the actual check, it should be:
{noformat}
The database is not using Unicode. Crucible requires that the database uses a UTF8 encoding to support internalization.
{noformat}

Allow the user to find files using ant globs.

Examples:
* {{\*\*/\*.xml}}
* {{/src/\*\*/search/\*.tag}}
* {{/\*/content/\*\*/\*.css}}
* {{/\*/content/\*\*/styl?-search.css}}

After indexing a new commit, the DirTreeCache is automatically invalidated:
{noformat}
2011-03-11 15:56:07,424 DEBUG [IncrementalPinger7 etsydev] fisheye.app DirTreeCache-invalidate - Invalidating cache for etsydev
{noformat}

This forces the checks for every top-level directories (the directories visible in the repository file list view "/fisheye/browse/myrepo"), to know if they are empty. For some pathological cases, this makes the page very slow. For example,

{noformat}
2011-03-11 15:56:29,597 DEBUG [btpool0-10 ] fisheye.perf DirTreeContextImpl$1-createValue - isempty check for /solr in 68254ms
{noformat}

Example: [FSH-5380|https://support.atlassian.com/browse/FSH-5380]
